@startuml stm_primary
title <<stm>> CRenderable Primary State Machine
skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor<<browse>> #e3f2fd
    BorderColor<<browse>> #1565c0
    FontColor<<browse>> #0d47a1
    BackgroundColor<<terminal>> #e8f5e9
    BorderColor<<terminal>> #2e7d32
}
skinparam shadowing false
top to bottom direction

state "pre_construct" as Pre <<browse>>
state "detached" as Detached <<browse>>
state "attached" as Attached <<browse>>
state "destroyed" as Dead <<terminal>>

Pre -down-> Detached : construct
Detached -down-> Attached : (CSceneView::AddRenderable via friend)
Attached --> Attached : set_color/set_alpha [invalidate]\nset_modelview / set_enabled [m_pView->Invalidate]\nset_centroid [no invalidate]\nset_object\ninvalidate [delete display lists]\ndraw_opaque/draw_transparent [empty base]\ndraw_*_list [lazy compile display list]
Detached --> Detached : set_color/alpha [Invalidate early-return]\nset_modelview/enabled [skip due to null m_pView]
Attached -down-> Dead : destruct
Detached -down-> Dead : destruct

note right of Attached
    Asymmetric invalidation:
    SetColor/Alpha -> full Invalidate
    (deletes display lists)
    SetModelview/Enabled -> only
    m_pView->Invalidate (display
    lists survive). Quirk.
end note
@enduml
